<p class="lead"><strong>Margins are the blank space around the edges of the page. The default setting is usually a margin of about one inch on all four sides. You can set the margin for each side separately. </strong></p class="lead">
	


<p>To set page margins for a spreadsheet, you use the same menu options as when you set page margins in Word Processing, using the <strong>Page Setup Options Box</strong>. How you access the Page Setup Options Box, depends upon your version of Excel.</p>




<hr>
<div class="row">
<div class="twelve columns">
<h4>Accessing the Page Setup Options Box from Microsoft Excel 2007/10 Ribbon</h4>


<p>In Microsoft Excel 2007/2010, preset margin options are easy to access on the ribbon. You can click on the downward facing arrow under Margins for these preset options. To look at the full options, we will access the Page Setup Options Box. Using the Page Setup Options Box, you can customize the page margins for the spreadsheet.</p>

<p> Click on the Page Layout Tab in the ribbon at the top of the spreadsheet.</p><p> In the Page Setup group, click on the downward facing arrow in the corner of the Page Setup group.</p><p> The Page Setup Options Box will open. </p>


