<div class="row">
<div class="twelve columns">
<h4>Page Setup Options Box in All Versions</h4>


<p>The <strong>Page Setup Options Box</strong> is the same for all versions of Excel, so let's look at the options you have to use it to customize page margins for spreadsheets.</p>

<p> There are four tabs at the top of the box: Page, Margins, Header/Footer and Sheet. The <strong>Margins Tab</strong> allows you to set the margins individually for each side of the spreadsheet as well as for the header and footer. You can center the whole spreadsheet, preview how the document will look and then print it.  </p>


<img class="img-wrap style1" src="images/spreadsheets/pagesetupmarginstab.jpg"/>



<ol>
<li>You can customize the setting for the <strong>left, right, top and bottom</strong> margins as well as the header and footer using the arrows next to each box or by typing a number in the box for each.</li>

<li>You can <strong>center</strong> the spreadsheet horizontally (between the top and bottom margins of the page), vertically (between the top and bottom margins of the page) by clicking on the box next each one. If you click on both boxes, the spreadsheet will be centered between all of the margins.</li>

<li>After you have made your selections, you can click on <strong>Print Preview</strong> to see how the spreadsheet will look when you print it.</li>
 
<li>If you want to print the spreadsheet, you can click on <strong>Print</strong>. </li>
</ol>

<p>When you are finished with your selections, click <strong>OK</strong>.</p>

